{{Infobox video game | title = Journey to the Center of the Earth | image = Journey to the Center of the Earth Coverart.png | alt = Cover art | caption = Cover art | developer = [[Human Soft]] | publisher = [[THQ]] | designer = | series = | engine = | released = {{vgrelease|EU|June 27, 2008}}{{vgrelease|NA|June 30, 2008|AUS|September 11, 2008}} | genre = [[Action game|Action]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] | platforms = [[Nintendo DS]] }}
'''''Journey to the Center of the Earth''''' (shortened as '''JCOE''') is an [[Action game]] for the [[Nintendo DS]] based on the movie: [[Journey to the Center of the Earth (2008 Hollywood film)|Journey to the Center of the Earth 3-D]] and is developed by American studio Human Soft and published by [[THQ]].<ref name="1up's preview of Journey to the Center of the Earth">{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/search?st=Journey+to+the+Center+of+the+Earth|title=1up's preview of Journey to the Center of the Earth|publisher=1up|accessdate=2008-07-03|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522142929/http://www.1up.com/do/search?st=Journey+to+the+Center+of+the+Earth|archivedate=2011-05-22|df=}}</ref><ref name="IGN's preview of Journey to the Center of the Earth">{{cite web|url=http://ds.ign.com/objects/142/14246945.html|title=IGN's look at Journey to the Center of the Earth |publisher=IGN|pages=One|accessdate=2008-06-28}}</ref>
''Journey to the Center of the Earth'' will allow the player to play as the three [[main characters]] of the movie: Trevor, Sean and Hannah as they journey to and through the center of the earth.<ref name="IGN's preview of Journey to the Center of the Earth"/> In the game the player will navigate their way through the center of the [[Earth]] in an attempt to escape.
== Gameplay == [[Image:JTTCOTE Screen.jpg|left|thumb|Trevor navigating through the center of the Earth]]
The gameplay of the game is based solely around the events of the movie in an open world environment, allowing the player to control out-of-control mine carts, and rafts throughout out the center of the [[Earth]].<ref name="IGN's JTTCOTE update">{{cite web|url=http://ds.ign.com/articles/869/869160p1.html|title=IGN's update of Journey to the Center of the Earth|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-07-03}}</ref> [[THQ]] also expanded the environment of the center of the Earth to allow the player to further journey throughout the open environment.<ref name="IGN's JTTCOTE update"/> The game also features three playable characters: Trevor, Sean and Hannah, who each have a special ability.<ref name="THQ official page for Journey to the Center of the Earth">{{cite web|url=http://www.playthq.com/games/gameinfo.php?id=1327|title=Play THQ/JTTCOTE|date=June 30, 2008|publisher=THQ|accessdate=2008-07-03|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218232820/http://www.playthq.com/games/gameinfo.php?id=1327|archivedate=December 18, 2008|df=}}</ref> Progress in the game is based on the use of [[checkpoint (video gaming)|checkpoint]]s.<ref name="IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth">{{cite web|url=http://ds.ign.com/articles/888/888074p1.html|title=IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-07-12}}</ref> Each time a character dies, they return to the last checkpoint and [[continue (video gaming)|continue]] from there.<ref name="IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth"/>''Journey to the Center of the Earth'' allows the player to control movements with the bottom screen while the character reacts on the upper screen. IGN said this about the game: "Horrible controls make the game an endless pattern of accidentally jumping into bottomless pits."<ref name="IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth"/>
== Enemies == * ''[[Allosaurus]]'' (boss) * [[Bat]] * ''[[Deinonychus]]'' * ''[[Dilophosaurus]]'' * ''[[Dimetrodon]]'' (boss) * ''[[Dunkleosteus]]'' * ''[[Euoplocephalus]]'' * [[Frilled lizard]] * ''[[Giganotosaurus]]'' (boss) * ''[[Ichthyosaurus]]'' * [[Monitor lizard]] * ''[[Plesiosaurus]]'' * ''[[Pteranodon]]'' * ''[[Pterodactylus]]'' * ''[[Stegosaurus]]'' * ''[[Triceratops]]'' * ''[[Tyrannosaurus]]'' (boss) * ''[[Velociraptor]]''
== Reception == {{Video game reviews | IGN = 3.5<ref name="IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth"/> }} [[IGN]] simply noted that "it's [the game] freaking terrible, and there's not even a console version to go play instead." IGN mainly criticized the game because there was only a version to play for the Nintendo DS and not on another platform. IGN also criticized the recordings of the game, saying that "The [[voice acting]] and [[sound effects]] for Center of the Earth are so horrendously bad that they literally made me [[LOL]]."<ref name="IGN's review of Journey to the Center of the Earth"/>
